headlines.description: E.C. Matthews scored 18 points, Jared Terrell had 16 and No. 22 Rhode Island beat VCU 81-68 on Friday night for its 14th consecutive victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Matthews, Terrell lead No. 22 URI past VCU, 81-68

video.headline: Rhode Island beats VCU for 14th straight win

headlines.description: Jerome Desrosiers' 3-pointer with 36 seconds left in overtime provided the winning points in Princeton's 76-73 victory over Yale on Friday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Desrosiers' 3 lifts Princeton over Yale in OT, 76-73

headlines.description: CJ Massinburg scored 26 points Friday night and Buffalo shot 59 percent from the field on its way to a 92-86 win over Western Michigan.
headlines.shortLinkText: Massinburg scores 26, Buffalo beats Western Michigan 92-86

headlines.description: Jesus Cruz's running floater in the paint with 2.1 seconds left gave Fairfield a 79-78 victory over Monmouth on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cruz's shot with 2.1 left gives Fairfield win over Monmouth

headlines.description: Nick Griffin scored 15 of his 20 points in the second half and Sam Idowu had 12 points to help Saint Peter's beat Niagara 58-52 on Friday night to snap a six-game skid.
headlines.shortLinkText: Griffin hits 4 3s, scores 20 as Saint Peter's beats Niagara

headlines.description: Pauly Paulicap had 13 points and 13 rebounds, Rich Williams added 10 points and 11 boards and Manhattan beat Siena 51-47 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Manhattan's late defense seals 51-47 win over Siena

headlines.description: Takal Molson and Jermaine Crumpton posted double-doubles and Canisius used a late surge to take a 73-67 victory over Marist on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Molson, Crumpton double-doubles lead Canisius to 73-67 win

headlines.description: Roland Griffin scored 18 of 20 points after halftime and finished with nine rebounds, Rickey McGill had 17 points, seven rebounds and eight assists and Iona beat Quinnipiac 87-82 in double overtime on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Griffin, McGill help Iona outlast Quinnipiac, 87-82, in 2OT

headlines.description: Caleb Wood had 17 of his 22 points during the second half and overtime to help Pennsylvania beat Brown 95-90 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Penn survives OT, beats Brown to stay undefeated in Ivy

video.headline: Penn Outlasts Brown, 95-90, in Overtime  - Via Ivy League

headlines.description: Quinton Adlesh scored 17 of his 20 points in the second half when Columbia charged back to hand Harvard its first Ivy League loss, 83-76, Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Adlesh, Columbia hand Harvard first Ivy loss of season 83-76

headlines.description: Matt Morgan scored 17 of his 28 points in the final 8 1/2 minutes and Joel Davis hit two free throws with 25 seconds left to help Cornell beat Dartmouth 86-85 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morgan, Davis help Cornell slip past Dartmouth, 86-85

headlines.description: Kameron Chatman had 21 points with eight rebounds to lead all five Detroit Mercy starters in double-figure scoring in a 74-60 victory over IUPUI on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Chatman scores 21 in Detroit Mercy's 74-60 victory

headlines.description: Bryce Nze had a career-high 25 points on 11-of-14 shooting to go with 10 rebounds on Friday night and Milwaukee beat Green Bay 76-58.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nze's career night leads Milwaukee over Green Bay 76-58

headlines.description: McKinley Wright scored 21 points, Lucas Siewert had 13 and Colorado held Utah to a season-low point total in beating the Utes 67-55 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Colorado holds Utah to season-low points in 67-55 victory

headlines.description: Tai Odiase had 19 points, on 8-for-8 shooting, and three blocks, Godwin Boahen hit four 3-pointers and finished with 16 points and Illinois-Chicago beat Oakland 79-73 on Friday night for its fifth win in a row.
headlines.shortLinkText: Odiase scores 19, UIC beats Oakland for fifth win in a row

nowFeed.headline: Under Sean Miller Deandre Ayton is maximizing his enormous potential. Ayton has always possessed the physical tools and a solid basketball IQ. He has worked hard at Zona along with making the adjustments to college basketball. For a freshman big man it's really hard to dominate right away. Since he arrived in the states he was a top ranked player in his class. Would have been top 5 in last years NBA draft. Now he will be a top 3 pick and will be much more prepared.

nowFeed.headline: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.
nowFeed.story: Cincinnati's loss at Houston will likely drop them from the No. 2-seed line in Joe Lunardi's Bracketology, with Texas Tech likely being the beneficiary to move up. The Cougars, who were a 10-seed coming into the night, scored another big resume win after picking one up over Wichita State in January.

nowFeed.headline: Houston upsets No. 5 Cincinnati 67-62, ending the Bearcats nation-leading 16-game winning streak. It's the first time the Cougars have beaten two top-10 opponents in a season since 1984.

nowFeed.headline: Ironically, Cincinnati's loss to Houston also finally gives Cincinnati its first win over a likely NCAA Tournament team.
